Massless is a very loose and somewhat deceiving term.  When we talk about mass, we talk about rest mass (also called invariant mass, intrinsic mass, or simply: mass).  Photons do not have rest mass because, well... they&#39;re never at rest.

What they do have is relativistic mass, where it&#39;s energy and momentum are related by E=pc (remember the mass-energy equivalence?).  Through derivations too long to note here, the magnitude of momentum is h/λ.  

